    {
      "step_id": "30e3704d",
      "step_index": 2,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Acidic group:** one **carboxylic acid** (`O=C(O)`), likely **deprotonated** at pH 7.4.\n- **Amide:** `CCC(=O)N1...` is a **lactam/amide**; **not basic** (amide N is not protonatable).\n- **Sulfonamide:** `S(=O)(=O)N3CCCCC3` is a **sulfonamide** attached to a **piperidine**.\n  - The sulfonamide **N** is not basic.\n  - The **piperidine nitrogen is sulfonylated**, so it is **not protonatable** (strongly deactivated; effectively neutral).\n- **Ring systems / lipophilicity:**\n  - One **fused bicyclic aromatic/heterocycle** (tetrahydroisoquinolinone-like core) providing an **aryl surface**.\n  - One **piperidine ring** (but neutral due to sulfonamide).\n- **H-bonding:**\n  - H-bond donors: **carboxylic acid OH** and **sulfonamide NH** (1 each).\n  - H-bond acceptors: carboxylate/acid O\u2019s, amide carbonyl O, sulfonyl O\u2019s (multiple acceptors).\n- **Structural alerts relevant to CYP2D6 inhibition:**\n  - **No free tertiary amine** (classic CYP2D6 inhibitor motif).\n  - No quinidine-like cationic center.",
      "tool_name": null,
