    },
    {
      "step_id": "a451059e",
      "step_index": 4,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "CYP2D6 inhibitors typically present:\n- A **protonatable basic N** (often tertiary amine) that can form a **salt bridge / ionic interaction** with **Asp301** in CYP2D6, anchoring the ligand.\n- One or more **lipophilic/aromatic rings** to occupy hydrophobic regions near the heme.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T19:45:27.519491+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "90e94e37",
      "step_index": 5,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "This molecule has **aromatic character**, but it **lacks a protonatable basic nitrogen**:\n- The only nitrogens are **amide** and **sulfonamide-linked piperidine N**, both **non-basic**.\n- Additionally, the **carboxylic acid** will be largely **anionic** at physiological pH, which tends to **reduce affinity** for the CYP2D6 active site (which often prefers cationic/basic substrates/inhibitors) and can reduce membrane partitioning into the enzyme environment.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T19:45:27.519521+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "5092e81e",
      "step_index": 6,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "So despite having an aromatic ring system, it is missing the **key cationic pharmacophore** that drives many CYP2D6 inhibitors.",
      "tool_name": null,
