      "content": "- **Typical CYP2D6 binding mode:** cationic N \u2194 **Asp301** + hydrophobic/aromatic packing near the heme, positioning for metabolism or tight inhibition.\n- **Here:** without a basic center, the molecule is less able to achieve the **electrostatic anchoring** that strongly contributes to CYP2D6 inhibition.\n- The **acidic/anionic character** may further bias binding away from the canonical CYP2D6 inhibitor pose and may favor other CYPs or show weak/non-specific binding at best.",
