      "content": "- **Potential counterargument:** The molecule is fairly functionalized and aromatic; some CYP inhibition can occur via **non-basic, hydrophobic binding** or via **tight binding** driven by shape complementarity.\n- **Why I still predict negative:** CYP2D6 inhibition is unusually dependent on a **protonatable nitrogen** for high-affinity binding; this structure is effectively **neutral/anion-dominant** at pH 7.4 with **no basic anchor**, making strong CYP2D6 inhibition less likely.\n- **Uncertainty:** Without calculated pKa/logP and experimental data, weak inhibition (e.g., at high \u00b5M) can\u2019t be excluded.",
